cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on interference management techniques in OFDMA-based cellular networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a SINR-proportional resource allocation strategy, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the sum-rate and coverage benefits of FFR, which are relevant to multimedia applications in cellular networks. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper analyzes the performance of FFR in a Poisson point process model, which is related to social and information networks. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper evaluates the relative merits of different frequency reuse strategies, which can be viewed as a game-theoretic problem.
